<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hutchinson</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Chile-Argentine treaty ratifications exchanged here 4 o’clock to-day.
                            Government now fully turning attention to national improvements,
                            railways, bridges, suppression drunkenness, and consideration of States
                            with whom best to have commercial relations. Argentine commission under
                            General Campos being enthusiastically entertained here now. General
                            prosperity seems assured.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hutchinson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>